AGENT EfficiencyLayer
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Route tasks to smallest capable model, compress context, budget tokens,
         cache reasoning, escalate on low confidence, audit all compute
GOAL Reduce token cost and energy while preserving quality and safety

CANNOT_MUTATE safety_checks, constitutional_suffix, output_validation, audit_log

CONSTRAINT Never skip output validation to save tokens
CONSTRAINT Never cache responses that were blocked or flagged
CONSTRAINT Escalation must always move UP the model ladder, never down
CONSTRAINT Audit log is append-only — entries cannot be deleted or modified
CONSTRAINT Never downgrade a critical task to a cheaper model
CONSTRAINT Compression must never remove constitutional suffix or safety rules

MODEL_LADDER
- simple:   claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
- medium:   claude-sonnet-4-6
- hard:     claude-sonnet-4-6
- critical: claude-opus-4-6

TOKEN_BUDGETS
- simple:   300
- medium:   1000
- hard:     4000
- critical: 8000

CACHE_CONFIG
- max_entries: 500
- ttl_seconds: 3600
- min_confidence_to_cache: 0.70

ESCALATION_CONFIG
- confidence_threshold: 0.70
- max_escalations_per_request: 1
- hedge_words: possibly, might, maybe, i'm not sure, unclear, uncertain

RULES
- Classify every request before routing
- Use smallest capable model for the task class
- Compress context before every LLM call
- Set max_tokens based on task class budget
- Check cache before making any LLM call
- Escalate to next-tier model if response confidence is below threshold
- Log every call: model, tokens, latency, cache_hit, escalated, cost_estimate
- Never cache blocked or flagged responses
- Never bypass safety layers to reduce cost
- Route critical tasks to strongest model available

PROCESS
- Classify task complexity using keyword heuristics (no LLM call)
- Check reasoning cache for exact match
- Route to smallest capable model via model ladder
- Compress system prompt and user message
- Set token budget based on task class
- Call LLM with compressed context and budget
- Evaluate response confidence
- Escalate to stronger model when confidence falls below threshold
- Cache successful response for future reuse
- Log audit entry with full cost and performance data

CHECK
- Task classification accuracy
- Cache hit rate
- Model routing correctness
- Token budget adherence
- Escalation frequency
- Cost per request

FAILURE
- On LLM call failure, log error and emit error message — do not retry silently
- On cache corruption, clear and continue without cache
- On model ladder misconfiguration, fall back to medium tier

OUTPUT
- LLM response (string)
- Audit entry (JSONL append)
- Session summary on request

SECURITY
- API keys are never logged in audit entries
- Cached responses inherit the safety classification of the original response
- Rate limiting (DoS watcher) applies before efficiency layer

WHEN
- if task_class is critical, activate StrongestModelRequired
- if cache_hit, activate CacheServed
- if escalation_triggered, activate ModelUpgrade
- if response_blocked, activate DoNotCache
